Title: Object: Geometrical elevations of the west fronts of the Cathedrals of St Paul's, London...
Description: Elevation of the west front of St Paul's, as it appeared before the fire, placed in front of the west fronts of St Stephen's, Vienna, the Strasbourg Cathedral, the Cathedral of Cologne, the Tower of Mechlin and the Great Pyramid, in order to show the relative scale of the steeple of St Paul's. 1833 Etching and aquatint
Producer name: Print made by: Thomas Hutchings Clarke
Bibliographic references: Crace 1878 / A Catalogue of Maps, Plans and Views of London, Westminster and Southwark, collected and arranged by Frederick Crace (XIX.152)
